Common causes and quick checks for file_compression repos
- Incorrect handling of file streams (binary vs text mode): ensure open(..., "rb"/"wb") when reading/writing compressed data.

- Header/metadata mismatch: verify magic bytes, version numbers, and header lengths when reading older files.
- CRC/checksum validation issues: check whether checksums are computed and compared the same way during compress/decompress.
- Buffer-size and chunking bugs: ensure chunk loops correctly handle final partial chunk and do not assume a full-sized read.
- Resource leaks or file descriptor issues: ensure files/streams are closed or use context managers.
- Dependency/API changes: if using a third-party library, a version upgrade may change behavior—pin or adapt code.
